how to start a project django on linux
- check python 3.4.3 min
  $ python3 --version
      python 3.4.3
  ohterwise: $ sudo apt-get install python 3.4
- create virtual environement
  create the repository of the project (mkdir)
  $ python3 -m venv myvenv
    if ubuntu: use virtualenv
      $ sudo apt-get install python-virtualenv
      $ virtualenv --python=python3.5 myvenv
- open the virtual envi "myvenv"
  $ source myvenv/bin/activate
  or $ . myvenv/bin/activate
- install django
  $ pip install django
  or $ pip install django~=version
- $ django-admin startproject projectname
  will create a new repository projectname
- $ django-admin startproject projectname .
  will create the project in the actual repository
      
